name: Lay Down the Law
text: Tradeable Set a minion's Attack and Health to 1. Quickdraw: Then deal 1 damage to it.
flavorText: The official term for "Because I said so!".

name: Lead Dancer
text: Deathrattle: Summon a minion from your deck with less Attack than this minion.
flavorText: "Follow my lead!" *dies*

name: Leeroy Jenkins
text: Charge. Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Whelps for your opponent.
flavorText: At least he has Angry Chicken.

name: Lesser Amethyst Spellstone
text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. (Take damage from your cards to upgrade.)
flavorText: A purple stone Azari carved For dark hearts, craving, power-starved. The first to bow, the warlock Rin, Embraced the darkness, slew her kin.

name: Lesser Diamond Spellstone
text: Resurrect 2 different friendly minions. (Cast 4 spells to upgrade.)
flavorText: A diamond, white, this stone the eighth A precious jewel for those of faith A whispered prayer restores the lost But none among them know the cost.

name: Lesser Emerald Spellstone
text: Summon two 3/3 Wolves. (Play a Secret to upgrade.)
flavorText: An emerald stone for Tauren hands Who sought its strength to save their lands Their tribes now lost, their rage released Who’s hunting now? And who’s the beast?

name: Lesser Jasper Spellstone
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. (Gain 3 Armor to upgrade.)
flavorText: In ancient woods, elves fought the curse The demon’s shadow to disperse But hatred raged and frail souls turned Now horned and hooved their forests burned.

name: Lesser Opal Spellstone
text: Draw 1 card. (Attack with your hero (time, times) to upgrade.)
flavorText: For those seeking glory and power Be not swayed by Azari the Devourer The opal grants victory to the weak But leaves your soul barren and bleak

name: Lesser Spinel Spellstone
text: Give Undead in your hand +1/+1. (Gain (Corpse, Corpses) to upgrade.)
flavorText: A story concluded, the kobolds had fought Yet here is a spellstone Azari forgot Pawned off to shops, considered a trinket Dark powers contained, none would think it

name: Li'Na, Shop Manager
text: Whenever you cast a spell, fill your board with random minions of that Cost.
flavorText: Somebody has to do the paperwork around here.

name: Lifebinder's Gift
text: Choose One - Get 2 random Nature spells; or Reduce the Cost of spells in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Everyone's investing in Nature spells these days, but that bubble is about to burst.

name: Lifedrinker
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
flavorText: In a pinch, he'll also settle for Holy Water: Zero.

name: Lightbomb
text: Deal damage to each minion equal to its Attack.
flavorText: This is what happens when you allow goblins to be priests.

name: Lightning Bolt
text: Deal 3 damage. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

name: Lightning Reflexes
text: Discover a Nature spell. If you play it this turn, Discover another.
flavorText: If you can dodge a lightning bolt, you can dodge a ball.

name: Lightning Storm
text: Deal 3 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (1)
flavorText: An umbrella won't be effective, I'm afraid.

name: Lightshow
text: Shoot beams at enemies that each deal 2 damage. Your future Lightshows shoot one more beam.
flavorText: Always remember P.L.U.R.: Peace, Laser-beams, Unity, Respect.

name: Linedance Partner
text: Battlecry: If you're holding another 3-Cost card, summon a random 3-Cost minion.
flavorText: Where did you come from? (Linedance Partner's Battlecry) Where did you go? (Face)

name: Living Horizon
text: Taunt, Divine Shield Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
flavorText: Even in the darkest of days, the sun never sets on the Badlands.

name: Living Prairie
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, summon two 3/3 Cows with Rush.
flavorText: Whoooooa, we're half way there Whooa-oh, -

name: Living Roots
text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage; or Summon two 1/1 Saplings.
flavorText: 2 out of 2 saplings recommend that you summon the saplings.

name: Load the Chamber
text: Deal 2 damage. Your next Naga, Fel spell, and weapon cost (1) less.
flavorText: Wait! Before we duel, I gotta install these shaders.

name: Loken, Jailer of Yogg-Saron
text: Battlecry: Discover a minion from your deck. Summon a Tentacle with its stats and Taunt.
flavorText: Really great at his job! - Yogg-Saron

name: Loot Hoarder
text: Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: Always roll need.

name: Lord Jaraxxus
text: Battlecry: Equip a 3/8 Blood Fury.
flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

name: Love Everlasting
text: Your first spell each turn costs (2) less. Lasts until you don't play a spell on your turn.
flavorText: Poison Bloom was accused of plagiarizing the "Ooh, how long can this go on (ooh yeah)" hook from an old-school musical group called The Saronite Chain Gang.

name: MC Blingtron
text: Battlecry: Both players equip 1/2 Microphones. Your opponent's increases all damage they take by 1!
flavorText: If this is the outcome of the robot uprising, then sign me up!

name: Mad Bomber
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage randomly split between all other characters.
flavorText: He's not really all that crazy, he is just not as careful with explosives as he should be.

name: Madame Lazul
text: Battlecry: Discover a copy of a card in your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Of course she knows the future, she’s been looking at your cards the WHOLE TIME!

name: Magatha, Bane of Music
text: Battlecry: Draw 5 cards. Give any spells drawn to your opponent.
flavorText: Not to be confused with that one other "-agatha" that likes when you play minions.

name: Magical Dollhouse
text: Gain Spell Damage +1 this turn only.
flavorText: Build your own dollhouse in 3 easy steps! 1. Build a castle. 2. Miniaturize it. 3. GLITTER!

name: Magtheridon, Unreleased
text: Dormant for 2 turns. While Dormant, deal 3 damage to all enemies at the end of your turn.
flavorText: Playing with this card can be penalized with up to a two-year suspension. Please wait until the card is officially released.

name: Malefic Rook
text: Battlecry: Attack YOUR hero.
flavorText: Was a regular Pawn but Fel in with the wrong toys.

name: Malfurion's Gift
text: Discover a temporary Feral Rage, Wild Growth, or Swipe.
flavorText: "May this imbue you with the life of the party!" -Malfurion

name: Malygos the Spellweaver
text: Battlecry: Draw spells until your hand is full.
flavorText: After many years, Malygos has decided mortals can use magic. ALL THE MAGIC!

name: Mana Geode
text: Overheal: Summon a 2/2 Crystal.
flavorText: Gadgetzan, where even the pet rocks have pet rocks.

name: Mantle Shaper
text: Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast while holding this.
flavorText: You got a fireplace? I've got a guy who shapes mantles.

name: Manufacturing Error
text: Draw 3 cards. If your deck has no minions, they cost (3) less.
flavorText: You thought the 9-piece puzzle would be easy, didn't you?

name: Mark of the Wild
text: Give a minion Taunt and +2/+3. (+2 Attack/+3 Health)
flavorText: Not to be confused with Jim of the Wild.

name: Marrow Manipulator
text: Battlecry: Spend up to 5 Corpses. Deal 2 damage to a random enemy for each.
flavorText: Also buffs your Calcium by 1000mg.

name: Maruut Stonebinder
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, Discover an Elemental to summon. Add the others to your hand.
flavorText: Savior of the World Pillar, Maruut valiantly fought the Twilight's Hammer to aid Therazane against the Cataclysm.

name: Master's Call
text: Discover a minion in your deck. If all 3 are Beasts, draw them all.
flavorText: "Hello? Yes, this is Huffer."

name: Maw and Paw
text: At the end of your turn, gain 5 Corpses. At the start of your turn, spend 5 Corpses to give your hero +5 Health.
flavorText: Home is where the disfigured, rotten heart is.

name: Mecha-Leaper
text: Magnetic Deathrattle: Give a friendly Mech +2/+2 and this Deathrattle.
flavorText: Now to find my Mecha-Macaw and my Mecha-Titus and we'll be Mecha-Set.

name: Mechagnome Guide
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell. Forge: It costs (3) less.
flavorText: Theme park? Tropical island? Fiery pit of despair? We've got something for everyone.

name: Meddlesome Servant
text: Battlecry: If you've cast 5 or more spells this game, draw 2 cards. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: Has successfully gotten away with it too.

name: Melomania
text: Each time you play a minion this turn, add a random Shaman spell to your hand.
flavorText: I once saw a horse that had watermelons for hair. It was a melon mane, ya?!

name: Melted Maker
text: After you Forge a card, get a copy of it.
flavorText: Melts what he makes (cheese) and makes a mean melt (grilled cheese).

name: Menacing Nimbus
text: Battlecry: Add a random Elemental to your hand.
flavorText: Electra stores her elementals in the cloud.

name: Merch Seller
text: At the end of your turn, put a random spell on the top of your opponent's deck.
flavorText: "Sorry, we're all out of Mediums. All we've got left are Gnome, Extra Large, and Annihilan."

name: Mes'Adune the Fractured
text: Battlecry: Draw an Elemental. Split it into two halves.
flavorText: Cracking open an elemental with the boys.

name: Messenger Buzzard
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Beast. Give minions in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: The bird brings the word (which happens to be bird).

name: Messmaker
text: Lifesteal, Taunt Deathrattle: Deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: The most painful 1 damage of your life.

name: Metamorphosis
text: Swap your Hero Power to "Deal 5 damage." After 2 uses, swap it back.
flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

name: Metrognome
text: After you play a -Cost card, draw a -Cost card. (Then increase!)
flavorText: He's very popular on Click-Clock.

name: Mic Drop
text: Draw 2 cards. Finale: Give your weapon +2 Attack.
flavorText: The perfect card to play after emoting.

name: Midnight Wolf
text: Rush Outcast: Summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Three of these would make for an EPIC T-shirt.

name: Might of Menethil
text: Battlecry: Spend up to 3 Corpses. Freeze that many enemy minions.
flavorText: Menethil's Might, at night, fights the light, not quite the blight, right?

name: Mimiron, the Mastermind
text: After you play a Mech, get a random one of Mimiron's Gadgets.
flavorText: 1N1T14T1NG F74V0R T3XT S3QU3NC3.

name: Mind Control Tech
text: Battlecry: If your opponent has 4 or more minions, take control of one.
flavorText: Mind Control technology is getting better, but that's not saying much.

name: Mindbender
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage for each card you have drawn this turn. ( )
flavorText: I like my brain unbent, thanks.

name: Minecart Cruiser
text: Rush, Overload: (2) Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, don't Overload.
flavorText: Where are you drivin', Minecart Cruiser? Where is your bounty, fortune, and fame?

name: Mining Casualties
text: Summon two 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits with "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Frail Ghoul".
flavorText: They'll be fiiiiiiiiine.

name: Minotauren
text: Rush Whenever this minion deals damage, gain that much Armor.
flavorText: "Why's he so mad?" "He's been stuck on one of Hearthstone's hidden maze puzzles for YEARS."

name: Miracle Salesman
text: Deathrattle: Get a Tradeable Snake Oil.
flavorText: "Hey! Hope you’re well. Have you ever wanted to be your own boss?"

name: Misfire
text: Deal 3, 2, and 1 damage to random minions. Quickdraw: Choose the targets.
flavorText: "Me should not have taken candle."

name: Mish-Mash Mosher
text: Rush After this attacks, gain +1 Attack and attack a random enemy minion.
flavorText: In the pit, he feels more alive than ever.

name: Mismatched Fossils
text: Discover a Beast and an Undead. Swap their stats.
flavorText: Whoever put these fossils together must be really careless.

name: Mister Mukla
text: Rush. Battlecry: Fill your opponent's hand with Bananas.
flavorText: Music is Mukla's escape from his anger. When he's on-stage, it's like he's a whole different gorilla… Until you boo him.

name: Mixtape
text: Discover a copy of a card your opponent played this game.
flavorText: That tape has got poetry and clarinet on it, Garona. POETRY. AND CLARINET.

name: Mo'arg Drillfist
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Excavate a treasure.
flavorText: Also functions as the town dentist.

name: Molten Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each damage your hero has taken.
flavorText: He gets terrible heartburn. BECAUSE HE IS FULL OF LAVA.

name: Molten Rune
text: Deal 3 damage. Get a random spell. Forge: This casts twice.
flavorText: It's post-ancient modern realist neoclassical impressionist art. No idea what it means though.

name: Momentum
text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Costs (1) less for each card you've drawn this turn.
flavorText: "Mass Times Velocity" wasn't as catchy.

name: Monstrous Form
text: Give a friendly minion +3/+3 until your next turn.
flavorText: Then, it lives. Horribly.

name: Mortal Coil
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If that kills it, draw a card.
flavorText: If your spells look like horrifying skulls, let's be honest, you should get to draw some cards.

name: Mortal Eradication
text: Deal 5 damage randomly split among all enemy minions. Restore 2 Health to your hero for each killed.
flavorText: Clearly anything with 6 or more health is immortal. Such as Street Trickster. We are nerfing Street Trickster for lore accuracy.

name: Mosh Pit
text: Spend 3 Corpses to give a friendly minion Reborn.
flavorText: Let the Corpses hit the floor!

name: Mountain Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
flavorText: His mother said that he was just big boned.

name: Muck Pools
text: Transform a friendly minion into one that costs (1) more.
flavorText: Making a dredger is easier than you'd think. You don't need to worry about mucking it up!

name: Murloc Tidecaller
text: Whenever you summon a Murloc, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: This guy gets crazy strong at family reunions.

name: Murloc Tidehunter
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Murloc Scout.
flavorText: "Death will rise, from the tides!"

name: Murloc Warleader
text: Your other Murlocs have +2 Attack.
flavorText: Do Murlocs ever get tired of making the same old sound? Nope! Mrglglrglglglglglglgl!

name: Murmy
text: Reborn
flavorText: Unlike other mummies, they rolled him up with rice, sliced cucumbers, and soy sauce on the side.

name: Muscle-o-Tron
text: Battlecry: Give all minions in your hand +1/+1. Forge: +2/+2 instead.
flavorText: Bro, do you even forge?

name: Muster for Battle
text: Summon three 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits. Equip a 1/4 Weapon.
flavorText: "I'm bringing the guacamole!" – One of the most successful (yet rare) Silver Hand rallying cries

name: Mystery Egg
text: Miniaturize Deathrattle: Get a copy of a random Beast in your deck. It costs (5) less.
flavorText: Which came first, the Mukla or the egg?

name: Mythical Terror
text: Lifesteal At the end of your turn, force all enemy minions to attack this.
flavorText: You cannot pet the Terror in Hearthstone.

name: Necrotic Mortician
text: Battlecry: If a friendly Undead died after your last turn, Discover an Unholy Rune card.
flavorText: Her hair, just like her name, is full of 'tic's.

name: Needlerock Totem
text: At the end of your turn, gain 2 Armor and draw a card.
flavorText: You put the Needlerock in to get the Bloodrock out.

name: Nerubian Egg
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 4/4 Nerubian.
flavorText: Eggs are a good source of protein and Nerubians.

name: Nerubian Swarmguard
text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon two copies of this minion.
flavorText: How long can this go on? Apparently even in death.

name: Nesting Golem
text: Deathrattle: Resummon this with -1/-1.
flavorText: NESTING GOLEEEEEEEEEEEEM!!!!!!! Eh… It just doesn't feel the same.

name: Night Elf Huntress
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to three different enemies. (You pick the targets!)
flavorText: A triple threat, all on her own.

name: Noble Minibot
text: Magnetic After this attacks, give a random minion in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: I always get the minibot with the wobbly wheel.

name: Norgannon
text: Titan After this uses an ability, double the power of the other abilities.
flavorText: His tremendous arcane magic was strong enough to save all of the spirits of the titans after Sargeras destroyed their physical forms.

name: Northern Navigation
text: Discover a spell from your deck. If it's a Frost spell, Freeze a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Leads directly to Greatfather Winter's workshop.

name: Nostalgic Clown
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: If you've played a higher Cost card while holding this, deal 4 damage.
flavorText: He used to be kind of corrupt, but now he performs purely for the fun of it.

name: Nostalgic Gnome
text: Miniaturize Rush. After this minion deals exact lethal damage on your turn, draw a card.
flavorText: She remembers Alterac Valley like it was 833 days ago.

name: Nostalgic Initiate
text: Miniaturize The first time you cast a spell, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Nostalgic Initiate: "Man I wish I could relive my college days..." Kel'thuzad: "Say no more."

name: Novice Zapper
text: Spell Damage +1 Overload: (1)
flavorText: The novices would prefer that he did not.

name: Noxious Cadaver
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to an enemy and your hero.
flavorText: Shouldn't have eaten that gas station sushi.

name: Nozdormu the Eternal
text: Start of Game: If this is in BOTH players' decks, turns are only 15 seconds long.
flavorText: Live life in the fast lane. As long as your opponent does too.

name: Oaken Summons
text: Gain 6 Armor. Summon a minion from your deck that costs (4) or less.
flavorText: The Guild used oak trees until they all turned to ash.

name: Oasis Outlaws
text: Discover a Naga. If you've played a Naga while holding this, reduce its Cost by (1).
flavorText: With their oasis polluted by the Bloodrock Mining Company, Snake Eyes has set aside her differences with the outlaws of the Badlands to put an end to Bloodrock's operation.

name: Observer of Mysteries
text: Battlecry: Cast 2 random Secrets. At the start of your turn, destroy them.
flavorText: Nobody tell him, but he still has his Secrets set to the "Try Me" mode.

name: Observer of Myths
text: After you summon a minion with more Attack than this, give all friendly minions +1 Attack.
flavorText: "Oh hey, look! A myth!"

name: Obsessive Fan
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. It has Stealth while this is alive.
flavorText: "Obsessed? No! I'm just really really really really really really really really really really into E.T.C.'s music and everything he says, does, thinks, lives, and breathes!"

name: Obsidian Revenant
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon two random Deathrattle minions that cost (3) or less.
flavorText: What is this? A Reven for Ants?!

name: Obsidian Statue
text: Taunt, Lifesteal Deathrattle: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: The original artist spent many hours with a fine chisel perfecting the facial expression for maximum tauntiness.

name: Odyn, Prime Designate
text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, after your hero gains Armor, they gain that much Attack for that turn.
flavorText: The best offense is a good defense. 30 defense to be exact.

name: Ogre-Gang Ace
text: Rush Whenever this attacks, gain Divine Shield. (50% chance to gain Lifesteal instead.)
flavorText: 100% chance to not play by the rules.

name: Ogre-Gang Outlaw
text: Rush 50% chance to attack the wrong enemy.
flavorText: Why don't they just buy another hat?

name: Ogre-Gang Rider
text: Rush 50% chance to give your hero +3 Attack this turn instead of attacking.
flavorText: Doesn't know his ride from his left.

name: Once Upon a Time...
text: Summon a random 3-Cost Beast, Dragon, Elemental, and Murloc.
flavorText: ...There was a humble little squirrel on a quest to defeat an evil dragon. With the help of its earthen friend, it saved the murloc princess from danger. The end.

name: One Hit Wonder
text: Rush Combo: Gain Poisonous.
flavorText: They're trying to get a second hit in with their next single, "Divine Shield".

name: Onyxia the Broodmother
text: At the end of each turn, fill your board with 1/1 Whelps.
flavorText: Throw more dots, throw more dots, more dots, more dots!

name: Opera Soloist
text: Battlecry: If you control no other minions, deal 3 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: It ain't over until the imp mother sings.

name: Origami Crane
text: Taunt Battlecry: Swap Health with another minion.
flavorText: I was born with 1-Health and paper skin.

name: Origami Dragon
text: Divine Shield, Lifesteal Battlecry: Swap stats with another minion.
flavorText: The fire will give you a papercut, which CAN burn. Does that count?

name: Origami Frog
text: Rush Battlecry: Swap Attack with another minion.
flavorText: For extra-realistic fly-snatching action, use tape!

name: Outfit Tailor
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Attack and Health equal to this minion's.
flavorText: She has this terrible habit of eating melted cheese while on the job.

name: Overdraft
text: Tradeable Unlock your Overloaded Mana Crystals to deal that much damage.
flavorText: Wait. It costs mana to be out of mana?!

name: Overflow Surger
text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this for each turn in a row you've played an Elemental. ( )
flavorText: The drip on this elemental is straight fire!

name: Overgrown Beanstalk
text: Summon a 2/2 Treant. Draw a card for each Treant you control.
flavorText: You'd need to be pretty jacked to climb this.

name: Overlord Runthak
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give +1/+1 to all minions in your hand.
flavorText: Knows how to lift everyone up while tearing every enemy down.

name: Owlonius
text: Spell Damage +1 Your spells get double bonus from Spell Damage.
flavorText: They said you sound like an owl.

name: Pack the House
text: Summon a random 6, 5, 4, and 3-Cost minion. Overload: (2)
flavorText: How many Pack the Houses would a pack house if a pack could house Pack the House?

name: Painted Canvasaur
text: Battlecry: Give each other friendly Beast a random bonus effect.
flavorText: Oh this is a present? Would you like that gift raptor not?

name: Painter's Virtue
text: Lifesteal After your hero attacks, give minions in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: For when the Light hits the painting at a certain angle.

name: Paparazzi
text: Battlecry: Discover a Legendary minion.
flavorText: When you're a Legendary minion, you get a shiny orange gem, a dragon emblem, and about 100 of these people following you everywhere.

name: Papercraft Angel
text: Your Hero Power costs (0).
flavorText: Warcraft. StarCraft. And now, Papercraft!

name: Parched Desperado
text: Battlecry: If you've cast a spell while holding this, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: I'm green And I'm about to die Da ba dee da ba di

name: Park Panther
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Somebody called animal control once. It didn't work out very well for anybody.

name: Party Animal
text: Battlecry: Give +1/+1 to each minion of a different type in your hand.
flavorText: He's the wildlife of the party!

name: Patchwork Pals
text: Get all 3 Animal Companions. They cost (1) less.
flavorText: "I'll name you Misha, you Huffer, and you can be the third one."

name: Peaceful Piper
text: Choose One - Draw a Beast; or Discover one.
flavorText: "Is there anything worth more than peace and love on the planet Azeroth?"

name: Pendant of Earth
text: Discover a minion from your deck. Restore Health to your hero equal to its Cost.
flavorText: Eaaaarrrrthhhhhh Pendaaaannnttttt Poweeerrrrrrrrrrr!!!!!!!!

name: Photographer Fizzle
text: Battlecry: Take a Snapshot of your current hand and shuffle it into your deck.
flavorText: Look at this photograph.

name: Pile of Bones
text: Deathrattle: The next time you Excavate, resummon this.
flavorText: It's a very well-organized pile, I'll give you that.

name: Pip the Potent
text: Battlecry: Copy each 1-Cost card in your hand.
flavorText: One time, I was trying to get Pip's attention to warn her that the dangerous outlaw Cheery Ollie, who also goes by just 'O', was headed her way. "Pip! Pip! Cheery O!", I shouted.

name: Pipsi Painthoof
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random Divine Shield, Rush, and Taunt minion from your deck.
flavorText: "Earthmother guide my paintbrush strokes, especially on the eyes."

name: Pit Stop
text: Discover a Mech from your deck. Give it +2/+1.
flavorText: "Guido! It's time."

name: Plagiarizarrr
text: Battlecry: Get a copy of the top card of your opponent's deck.
flavorText: He's also working on his own Hearthstone expansion: Festival of Epics.

name: Plagued Grain
text: Gain 4 Corpses. Shuffle four Crates into your deck that summon a 2/2 Undead when drawn.
flavorText: Oh, don’t mind the smell. They're just aged!

name: Plated Beetle
text: Deathrattle: Gain 3 Armor.
flavorText: "Ok, your party has defeated the beetle." "I put it on my head." "What?" "I put it on my head. Like a hat."

name: Playhouse Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each card you've drawn this game.
flavorText: WARNING: NOT A PLAYHOUSE. DO NOT ATTEMPT TO CLIMB.

name: Plucky Paintfin
text: Poisonous Battlecry: Draw a Rush minion.
flavorText: Not everyone can become a great painter. But a great painter can come from anywhere.

name: Pocket Sand
text: Deal 3 damage. Quickdraw: Your opponent's next card costs (1) more.
flavorText: I was only trying to get it in your eyes, man. YOU didn't need to open your mouth like that!

name: Pop'gar the Putrid
text: Your Fel spells cost (2) less and have Lifesteal. Battlecry: Get two Barrels of Sludge.
flavorText: All around the arid badlands The Outlaws chased the Townsfolk Gerry had a train full of sludge POP! goes the sludge train

name: Pop-Up Book
text: Deal 2 damage. Summon two 0/1 Frogs with Taunt.
flavorText: What's up-book?

name: Popular Pixie
text: Choose One - Refresh your Hero Power; or Your next one costs (0).
flavorText: Popular Pixie personally prefers particularly powerful pop performances.

name: Posse Possession
text: Summon a 4/4 copy of a random minion in your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Keep your friends close, your enemies closer, and your shadows at gunpoint.

name: Power Chord: Synchronize
text: Choose a minion. Add a copy of it to your hand. Finale: Give both +1/+2.
flavorText: "It's all about you, girl On your 16,000th birthday"

name: Power Slider
text: Rush. Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each minion of a different type you've played this game. ( )
flavorText: There's a huge difference between a battle-axe and an axe-guitar. One is for combat, and the other is for combat AND rocking out.

name: Power of the Wild
text: Choose One - Give your minions +1/+1; or Summon a 3/2 Panther.
flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

name: Pozzik, Audio Engineer
text: Battlecry: Add two 3/3 Bots to your opponent's hand. Deathrattle: Summon them for yourself.
flavorText: "I'm down here, fixin' all the Gnomish tech that breaks down mid-set while that buffoon Fizzle is up there taking pictures of the sky. YOU tell ME who's the better engineer!"

name: Preparation
text: The next spell you cast this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: "Be Prepared" - Rogue Motto

name: Primordial Drake
text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: Before he became a rap artist.

name: Primordial Glyph
text: Discover a spell. Reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: It's the Ancient Tol'vir symbol for "Whoops!"

name: Prismatic Beam
text: Deal 3 damage to all enemy minions. Costs (1) less for each enemy minion.
flavorText: Seven colors of the rainbow, one for each enemy minion.

name: Prison Breaker
text: Battlecry: If you've cast 5 or more spells this game, deal 2 damage to all enemies. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: Flavor fail! Demolition Renovator did it FIRST!

name: Prison of Yogg-Saron
text: Choose a character. Cast 4 random spells (targeting it if possible).
flavorText: "We've finally captured Yogg-Saron! How should we keep him contained?" "How about... an open pit... right below us... with four loose chains?" "PERFECT!"

name: Prosthetic Hand
text: Magnetic, Reborn Can Magnetize to Mechs or Undead.
flavorText: It's creaky and it's rusty! It's spooky and it's dusty!

name: Psychic Conjurer
text: Battlecry: Copy a card in your opponent’s deck and add it to your hand.
flavorText: "I see... a WISP? Why do you have a wisp?!"

name: Puppet Theatre
text: Choose an enemy minion. Get a 1/1 copy of it that costs (1).
flavorText: AUDIENCE PARTICIPATION TIME!

name: Puppetmaster Dorian
text: After you draw a minion, get a 1/1 copy of it that costs (1).
flavorText: Though Dorian may officially be working under Dr. Boom, we all know who's really pulling the strings...

name: Purifying Power
text: Silence all friendly minions, then give them +1/+2.
flavorText: I sure do love making my minions better!

name: Puzzlemaster Khadgar
text: Battlecry: Equip a 0/6 Wisdomball that casts helpful Mage spells!
flavorText: Khadgar Khadgar in the ball, who is the smartest white-haired, tall, handsome mage of them all?

name: Pyrotechnician
text: After you cast a spell, add a random Fire spell to your hand.
flavorText: The difference between a pyrotechnician and a pyromaniac is a paycheck.

name: Quality Assurance
text: Draw 2 Taunt minions.
flavorText: I assure you this card is quality.

name: Quartzite Crusher
text: Lifesteal. Freeze any character damaged by your hero.
flavorText: It's not just a weapon… it's a rock!

name: Quick Pick
text: After your hero attacks, draw a card.
flavorText: QUICK! Pick which quick pick trick will stick in the thick of the wick! Lickety split!

name: Quick Shot
text: Deal 3 damage. If your hand is empty, draw a card.
flavorText: Han shot first.

name: R.C. Rampage
text: Summon six 1/1 Hounds. Any that can't fit give the others +1/+1.
flavorText: This place has really gone to the dogs.

name: Ra-den
text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Summon each other minion you've played this game that did not start in your deck.
flavorText: Regularly participates in Immortal Combat.

name: Raging Felscreamer
text: Battlecry: The next Demon you play costs (2) less.
flavorText: Screaming loudly will not reduce the cost of non-demonic goods.

name: Ragnaros the Firelord
text: Can't attack. At the end of your turn, deal 8 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: Ragnaros was summoned by the Dark Iron dwarves, who were eventually enslaved by the Firelord. Summoning Ragnaros often doesn’t work out the way you want it to.

name: Raid Leader
text: Your other minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: "That's a 50 DKP minus!"

name: Raiding Party
text: Draw 2 Pirates from your deck. Combo: And a weapon.
flavorText: And a bowl of chips. And some of those little cocktail weenies!

name: Rainbow Seamstress
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with a Blood, Frost, or Unholy card, gain Lifesteal, Reborn, or Rush respectively.
flavorText: Is this card any good? It would seam sew.

name: Rambunctious Stuffy
text: Rush After you cast a Frost spell, gain Reborn.
flavorText: The Lich King can't sleep without his stuffy.

name: Rat Trap
text: Secret: After your opponent plays three cards in a turn, summon a 6/6 Rat.
flavorText: MISSING: One giant rat. Please return to King Togwaggle.

name: Raven Idol
text: Choose One - Discover a minion; or Discover a spell.
flavorText: Was petrified when it found out it didn't make the cut for Azerothian Idol.

name: Ravenous Kraken
text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly minion. Deathrattle: Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: He's witewally hitting the squiddy wight now.

name: Raza the Resealed
text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, your Hero Power refreshes whenever you play a card.
flavorText: The 10th anniversary edition of a classic bestseller!

name: Razorfen Rockstar
text: After you gain Armor, gain 2 more.
flavorText: Quilboar feel Rock in their blood. And blood in their rocks.

name: Razorscale
text: Cards can't cost less than (2).
flavorText: A razorscale, razormane, and razorclaw walk into the tavern.

name: Reap What You Sow
text: Deal 3 damage. Excavate a treasure.
flavorText: With a hat like that, I'd say their tailor did all of the sowing.

name: Record Scratcher
text: Deathrattle: Refresh Mana (Crystal, Crystals). (Play Combo cards while equipped to improve!)
flavorText: A Rogue's favorite audio sample is an orchestral stab.

name: Red Card
text: Make a minion go Dormant for 2 turns.
flavorText: Finally, Demon Hunter has expanded its color palette to TWO colors!

name: Redgill Razorjaw
text: Rush
flavorText: One fish, two fish, red fish replaces blue fish.

name: Rehydrate
text: Restore 7 Health. Quickdraw: Refresh 2 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Just doing our part as the Hearthstone development team in reminding you to drink more water!

name: Reinforced Plating
text: Gain 6 Armor. Excavate a treasure.
flavorText: I am become death, destroyer of azerite.

name: Relentless Worg
text: Rush After this attacks and kills a minion, restore this to full Health.
flavorText: It's the Year of the Worg! Wait - what do you mean 'wolf'?

name: Reliquary Researcher
text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, cast two random Mage Secrets.
flavorText: What good is a researcher if they're just gunna keep it all a secret?

name: Remixed Dispense-o-bot
text: Gains an extra effect in your hand that changes each turn.
flavorText: "Mine gave me free money!" "Mine gave me free ice cream!" "… mine gave me two sheep that explode. They were free but I still want a refund."

name: Remixed Musician
text: Rush Gains an extra effect in your hand that changes each turn.
flavorText: Like every bard I know, he's a chaotic Neutral jack of all trades.

name: Remixed Rhapsody
text: Deal 3 damage to all minions. Gains an extra effect in your hand that changes each turn.
flavorText: "Is this real life?" "No, this is a card game."

name: Remixed Totemcarver
text: Gains an extra effect in your hand that changes each turn.
flavorText: Music always sounds better on old, wooden speakers.

name: Remixed Tuning Fork
text: Gains an extra effect in your hand that changes each turn.
flavorText: You can tune a fork, but you can't tune a fish.

name: Remorseless Winter
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies. Draw a card.
flavorText: In the Badlands, this is a Rare.

name: Remote Control
text: After your hero attacks, summon a 1/1 Hound.
flavorText: For some reason, my dog keeps trying to eat this.

name: Reno, Lone Ranger
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, empty the enemy board and limit it to 1 space for a turn.
flavorText: With an uncertain past and a questionable future, Reno was lucky to find his home on the range.

name: Repackage
text: Stuff all minions into a 2-Cost Box, then shuffle it into the opponent's deck.
flavorText: I don't want to play with you anymore.

name: Replicating Menace
text: Magnetic Deathrattle: Summon three 1/1 Microbots.
flavorText: It's a car! *Whomp whomp whomp* It's a robot! *Whomp whom-CRUNCH* It's… three.. smaller robots!

name: Resistance Aura
text: Your opponent's spells cost (1) more. Lasts enemy turns.
flavorText: Perfect for defending against Beasts. Specifically small ones. Like, a very specific species of small insectoid animal. Ants. It resists ants.

name: Reska, the Pit Boss
text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each minion that died this game. Deathrattle: Take control of a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Overseer of the Bloodrock Mine, Reska will work you to the bone. They'll then reanimate your bones and work THOSE bones to the bone.

name: Reverberations
text: Summon a copy of a minion. Each one dies after taking damage.
flavorText: This sounds much louder in the void.

name: Rewind
text: Discover a copy of another spell you've cast this game.
flavorText: If you don't find the spell you want, just cast this one more time and see if you get lucky.

name: Rexxar's Gift
text: Discover a temporary Quick Shot, Deadly Shot, or Explosive Shot.
flavorText: "I shop alone." -Rexxar

name: Rheastrasza
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, summon the Purified Dragon Nest.
flavorText: Rheastrasza ascends above loyalty to just her dragonflight to serve all dragonkind. She believes all flights deserve a future and will give her life for the future dragon prince.

name: Rhyme Spinner
text: Rush Combo: Gain +1/+1 for each other Combo card you've played this game. ( )
flavorText: For ONCE we're not talking about ice!

name: Rhythm and Roots
text: Choose One (Secretly) - Summon three 5/5 Ancients in 2 turns; or 8/8 Giants in 4 turns.
flavorText: For Zok's latest song, he decided to go back to his roots. Like the ones on a tree. Tree roots.

name: Rhythmdancer Risa
text: Rush After your hero attacks, return this to your hand and set its Cost to (1).
flavorText: Shadowstep to the left! Double jump to the right! Class cross!

name: Righteous Protector
text: Taunt Divine Shield
flavorText: Original name was Tubular Protector, but this seems more bodacious.

name: Rin, Orchestrator of Doom
text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Both players draw 2 cards, discard 2 cards, and destroy the top 2 cards of their deck.
flavorText: Rin's orchestra is the best of the best. When your replacement is just one summoning away, you have to play perfectly.

name: Roaring Applause
text: Draw a card. Repeat for each minion of a different type you control.
flavorText: Please clap.

name: Rock Master Voone
text: Battlecry: Copy each minion of a different type in your hand.
flavorText: After several audience members were burnt to a crisp, Voone's band became a lot less all-in on Dragons.

name: Rolling Stone
text: Rush Battlecry: If the last card you played costs (1), gain +1/+1.
flavorText: Sadly, the mariachi band it used to play in gathers no más.

name: Rowdy Fan
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. It has +3 Attack while this is alive.
flavorText: "This song is so good, it makes me want to PUNCH SOMEONE IN THE FACE!!"

name: Rowdy Partner
text: Battlecry: If you're holding another 4-Cost card, deal 4 damage.
flavorText: Rowdy, partner!

name: Royal Librarian
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Silence a minion.
flavorText: Books on how to flip the Auction House are down that way.

name: Rumble Enthusiast
text: After you play the left- or right-most card in your hand, deal 1 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: There's always room for one more game in the tavern!

name: Runefueled Golem
text: Battlecry: Discover a weapon from any class.
flavorText: Hmm, glyph gauge is running low. Better fill up at the next town.

name: Runes of Darkness
text: Discover a weapon. Spend 3 Corpses to give it +1/+1.
flavorText: "Sorry, Squirmy. I'm working."

name: Runic Adornment
text: Discover a spell that costs (3) or less. Shuffle 2 copies into your deck that Cast When Drawn.
flavorText: Rune, rune on the wall, who's the greenest of them all?

name: Rush the Stage
text: Draw two Rush minions. They cost (1) less.
flavorText: Left Shark, get to the stage now!

name: Rustrot Viper
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Destroy your opponent's weapon.
flavorText: Poisonous to weapons.

name: SECURITY!!
text: Summon two 1/1 Illidari with Rush. Outcast: Summon one more.
flavorText: Check all of the boxes that contain VENGEANCE to play this card.

name: SI:7 Agent
text: Combo: Deal 2 damage.
flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

name: SP-3Y3-D3R
text: Magnetic Stealth for 1 turn.
flavorText: The itsy bitsy spider magnetized onto the water spout.

name: Saddle Up!
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a random Beast that costs (3) or less."
flavorText: And then they rode off into the sunset, not knowing they left their stove on.

name: Safety Goggles
text: Gain 6 Armor. Costs (0) if you don't have any Armor.
flavorText: Remember, always be safe in the lab to mitigate injuries! *painfully snaps goggles onto face*

name: Saloon Brewmaster
text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion to your hand. Give it +2/+2.
flavorText: Brewmaster Bru brought Barrelbrim bursting barrels of barely brewed barley brew. Barrelbrim bought Bru's barley brew, barring the barrels broken from the brazen brunch brawl.

name: Sand Art Elemental
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Give your hero +1 Attack and Windfury this turn.
flavorText: This art HURT ME!!!

name: Sandbox Scoundrel
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Your next card this turn costs (3) less.
flavorText: "Really? A bunch of fake plastic gems AGAIN!?"

name: Sanguine Depths
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: There may not be any skeletons in the closets at Castle Nathria, but there sure are souls in the basement.

name: Sanitize
text: Deal damage equal to your Armor to all minions. Forge: Gain 4 Armor first.
flavorText: We were originally going to make a joke about a popular streamer, but one of our designers is a total germaphobe.

name: Sap
text: Return an enemy minion to your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Rogues love sappy movies.

name: Sargeras, the Destroyer
text: Titan Battlecry: Open a portal that summons two 3/2 Imps each turn.
flavorText: Formerly the Defender of the Pantheon, he became disillusioned by his mission and formed the Burning Legion to destroy all life within the universe.

name: Saronite Shambler
text: Battlecry: If you've cast 5 or more spells this game, give your hero +4 Attack this turn. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: They play the best rock music at the saro-nite club.

name: Saronite Tol'vir
text: Taunt Whenever this is attacked, draw a card.
flavorText: Talk to the hand.

name: Savannah Highmane
text: Deathrattle: Summon two 2/2 Hyenas.
flavorText: In the jungle, the mighty jungle, the lion gets slowly consumed by hyenas.

name: Saxophone Soloist
text: Battlecry: If you control no other minions, add a Saxophone Soloist to your hand.
flavorText: He used to play to crowds of adoring Murlocs, but 20 years later all that's left is gigs at secluded clubs and regrets. Where did all the time go? His dreams of fame and fortune, snuffed out like the flame of a small candle in a dimly lit bar. Nothing but smoke in the wind.

name: Scale Replica
text: Draw your lowest and highest Cost Dragon.
flavorText: Get it!?! It's because dragons have hides - commonly known as scales - and this is a model of a dragon on a smaller level, also known as a scale. IT'S THE SAME WORD!

name: Scarab Keychain
text: Battlecry: Discover a 2-Cost card.
flavorText: "How do you keep losing your keys!? They couldn't have just gotten up and walked away!"

name: Screaming Banshee
text: Lifesteal After your hero gains Health, summon a Soul with that much Attack and Health.
flavorText: Her singing will be sure to wake you up (wake you up inside).

name: Sea Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each other minion on the battlefield.
flavorText: See? Giant.

name: Sen'jin Shieldmasta
text: Taunt
flavorText: Sen'jin Village is nice, if you like trolls and dust.

name: Serenity
text: Give all enemy minions -2 Attack. Destroy any with 0 Attack.
flavorText: Ra-den loves teaching yoga on his off-hours.

name: Shadestone Skulker
text: Rush. Battlecry: Take your weapon and gain its stats. Deathrattle: Give it back.
flavorText: Sharing is caring - and they don't care.

name: Shadow Ascendant
text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: When you're at the bottom, there's nowhere to ascend, but up.

name: Shadow Chord: Distort
text: Give a minion -5/-5. If it has 0 Attack, destroy it.
flavorText: For some unknown reason, using distortion intentionally in your music will attract hundreds of geckos to your location.

name: Shadow Word: Pain
text: Destroy a minion with 3 or less Attack.
flavorText: A step up from a spell cast by many beginning acolytes: "Shadow Word: Annoy".

name: Shadow Word: Ruin
text: Destroy all minions with 5 or more Attack.
flavorText: Discovered by a worgen priest after a giant spilled a drink on her new white robes.

name: Shadow Word: Steal
text: Return an enemy minion to YOUR hand.
flavorText: Anduin will literally take your stuff and say it's a Shadow Word.

name: Shadowstep
text: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
flavorText: Rogue dance troops will sometimes Shadowstep away at the end of a performance. Crowds love it.

name: Shadowtouched Kvaldir
text: Battlecry: Your next healing effect deals damage instead.
flavorText: Four out of five deck doctors say this works great with Reno Jackson!

name: Shale Spider
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, draw a card.
flavorText: The 2nd member of the VERY exclusive Is-Called-A-Spider-But-Isn't-A-Beast Club.

name: Shambling Zombietank
text: Taunt Battlecry: Spend 5 Corpses to summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Spider Tank in shambles.

name: Shapeless Constellation
text: Battlecry: Transform into an 8/8 copy of a random minion in your hand.
flavorText: Galaxy Brain.

name: Sharp-Eyed Seeker
text: Battlecry: If there is a card in your deck that didn't start there, draw it.
flavorText: If you give it treats, it will give you shiny objects!

name: Shattered Reflections
text: Choose a non-Titan minion. Add a copy of it to your deck and battlefield.
flavorText: Get mad at your mirror once, see Shattered Reflections forever :(

name: Shell Game
text: Get a random Epic, Rare, and Common card from other classes.
flavorText: I thiiink… It's under all three of 'em!

name: Sheriff Barrelbrim
text: Battlecry: If you have 20 or less Health, open the Badlands Jail.
flavorText: Is that Sheriff Barrelbrim, owner of the Badlands Barrelbuilding?

name: Shield Block
text: Gain 5 Armor. Draw a card.
flavorText: Shields were invented because Face Block is USELESS.

name: Shield Slam
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each Armor you have.
flavorText: "What is a better weapon? The sharp one your enemies expect, or the blunt one they ignore?" - The Art of Warrior, Chapter 9

name: Shimmer Shot
text: Deal 1 damage. Summon a random minion of that Cost.
flavorText: I hope I don't jinx the outcome.

name: Shining Sentinel
text: Taunt, Elusive Battlecry: Summon a copy of this.
flavorText: OMG, I FINALLY GOT A SHINING SENTINEL AFTER 3 PHASES AND 8192 RESETS!!!!!

name: Ship's Chirurgeon
text: After you summon a minion, give it +1 Health.
flavorText: Knows the answer to every medical question except how to pronounce his name.

name: Shock Hopper
text: Battlecry: Get a random Overload card.
flavorText: Who is shocked about a frog hopping?

name: Shooting Star
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and the minions next to it.
flavorText: Literally starstruck.

name: Shoplifter Goldbeard
text: After you summon a Pirate, summon a copy of it that attacks a random enemy, then dies.
flavorText: "Arr, this plunder be great for Cap'n Fourteeth's baby shower!"

name: Showdown!
text: Both players summon three 3/3 Outlaws. Give yours Rush.
flavorText: An epic confrontation between the outlaws and the in-laws.

name: Shroomscavate
text: Give a minion Divine Shield. Excavate a treasure.
flavorText: As Globb shroominated on his situation, toiling endlessly in the mushroom mines, he came to the startling realization. His boss wasn't a very fun guy.

name: Shudderblock
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Your next Battlecry triggers 3 times, but can't damage the enemy hero.
flavorText: Beware the hinges that pinch, the scales that splinter!

name: Siamat
text: Battlecry: Gain 2 of Rush, Taunt, Divine Shield, or Windfury (your choice).
flavorText: TAUNT. TAUNT.

name: Sickly Grimewalker
text: After you summon an Undead, give it Poisonous.
flavorText: Anyone want some CHEEEEEESE?

name: Sif
text: Spell Damage + (Improved by each spell school you've cast this game!)
flavorText: She is Sif. He is Malygos. They are not the same person. They may have similar spell damage, they may have similar colors but they are different nonetheless.

name: Sigil of Time
text: At the start of your next turn, draw 3 additional cards.
flavorText: Sigil of Right A Down Right A Down.

name: Silk Stitching
text: Choose a friendly minion. Discover a spell that costs (4) or less for it to cast when it dies.
flavorText: The slogan of their very exclusive sewing club is "You can't stitch with us."

name: Silver Serpent
text: Rush, Poisonous Quickdraw: Gain Immune this turn.
flavorText: Skilled at exploring hidden temples.

name: Silvermoon Portal
text: Give a minion +2/+2. Summon a random 2-Cost minion.
flavorText: What's Millhouse Manastorm doing in Silvermoon?

name: Sing-Along Buddy
text: Your Hero Power triggers twice.
flavorText: One of the buttons makes you sound JUST like Ragnaros. BY FIRE BE HEARD!

name: Sinister Soulcage
text: Give a friendly Undead +2/+2. Spend 5 Corpses to summon a copy of it.
flavorText: Also a pretty neat night light!

name: Siphon Soul
text: Destroy a minion. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

name: Sir Finley, the Intrepid
text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, transform all enemy minions into 1/1 Murlocs.
flavorText: And exactly how does Finley turn everyone into a murloc?

name: Skarr, the Catastrophe
text: Battlecry: Deal damage to all enemies (improved by each turn in a row you've played an Elemental).
flavorText: We're not in Karazhan anymore, Reno.

name: Skeletal Sidekick
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Undead +2 Attack.
flavorText: He's got your back. And your arm.

name: Skeleton Crew
text: Battlecry: Excavate a treasure. It costs (0).
flavorText: They don't sweat, breathe or need lit candles... what more could you ask?

name: Sketch Artist
text: Battlecry: Draw a Shadow spell. Get a temporary copy of it.
flavorText: Never ask an artist how many pieces they've finished.

name: Sky Mother Aviana
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 10 random Legendary minions into your deck. They cost (1).
flavorText: It's a bird! It's a plane! It's 10 copies of Leeroy Jenkins!

name: Slagmaw the Slumbering
text: Rush, Taunt Dormant for 6 turns. (Excavate to awaken 2 turns sooner!)
flavorText: You delved too greedily and too deep. You know what they awoke in the darkness of the Badlands: Rush and Taunt.

name: Slam
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, draw a card.
flavorText: "Dun da dun, dun da dun": if you've heard an ogre sing this, it's too late.

name: Sleepy Dragon
text: Taunt
flavorText: Local villagers call her "Naps Under the Mountain."

name: Sleet Skater
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Freeze an enemy minion. Gain Armor equal to its Attack.
flavorText: How do you do, fellow Ice Elementals?

name: Sludge on Wheels
text: Rush. Whenever this takes damage, get a Barrel of Sludge and add one to the bottom of your deck.
flavorText: Cruisin' for an oozin'.

name: Smelt
text: Give a random minion in your hand +3/+3. Lose 3 Armor to do it again.
flavorText: Due to his heightened olfactory system, Kha'zgoroth is cursed with always being the one that dealt it.

name: Smokestack
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If it dies, Excavate a treasure.
flavorText: Don't worry, it's green energy!

name: Snake Eyes
text: Battlecry: Roll two dice, then Discover two cards of those Costs. (Doubles get an extra Discover!)
flavorText: Hey, put ALL of your hands on the table!

name: Snake Oil Seller
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 2 Tradeable Snake Oils into your opponent's deck.
flavorText: This oil is absolutely essential to your gameplan.

name: Snakebite
text: Rush Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each minion that died this turn. ( )
flavorText: Don't look her in the eyes or you'll turn to ROCK!

name: Sneaky Snakes
text: Summon two 1/1 Snakes with Stealth.
flavorText: You're a sneaky lil snake, aren'tcha?

name: Snowflipper Penguin
flavorText: On land, a group of penguins is called a "waddle."

name: Snuggle Teddy
text: Gigantify Elusive, Lifesteal, Taunt
flavorText: Someone really put their heart into making this.

name: Son of Hodir
text: Battlecry: Shuffle four 8/8 Giants into your deck that are summoned when drawn.
flavorText: You look dehydrated, drink some water! Come on, chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

name: Sonya Waterdancer
text: After you play a 1-Cost card, get a copy of it that costs (0).
flavorText: Water you dancing to?

name: Soulbreaker
text: After your hero attacks and kills a minion, gain 2 Corpses.
flavorText: Two for one special!

name: Soulburner Varia
text: After a friendly Undead dies, deal 2 damage to the enemy hero and get a random Shadow Priest spell.
flavorText: Captain's Log. 8/11/2023 There are 60 minutes remaining until the Flavor Text is due. It is Friday at 4 PM. We are out of stamina and ideas. Please send funnies, punnies, quippies, or your finest hahas. - The Design Team

name: Soulfreeze
text: Freeze a minion and its neighbors. Deal damage to your hero equal to the number Frozen.
flavorText: An effective way to freeze someone's soul is to just freeze their body.

name: Soulstealer
text: Battlecry: Destroy all other minions. Gain 1 Corpse for each enemy destroyed.
flavorText: "Wanna see what destruction looks like? Here it is in undead form - it's your boy Soulstealer!"

name: Southsea Captain
text: Your other Pirates have +1/+1.
flavorText: When he saves enough plunder, he's going to commission an enormous captain's hat. He has hat envy.

name: Southsea Deckhand
text: Has Charge while you have a weapon equipped.
flavorText: Pirates are into this new fad called "Planking".

name: Sparkling Phial
text: Deal 2 damage. Your next card this turn costs that much less.
flavorText: Lemme pull up your phial.

name: Speaker Stomper
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Enemy spells cost (2) more next turn.
flavorText: Just like in Hoofloose.

name: Spectral Cutlass
text: Lifesteal Whenever you play a card from another class, gain +1 Durability.
flavorText: So sharp it can cut through a spectral tomato!

name: Spectral Sight
text: Draw a card. Outcast: Draw another.
flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

name: Spikeridged Steed
text: Give a minion +2/+6 and Taunt. When it dies, summon a Stegodon.
flavorText: What beats cavalry? Dinosaur cavalry.

name: Spinetail Drake
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, deal 5 damage to an enemy minion.
flavorText: Mortal enemy of Cactus Cutter.

name: Spirit Bomb
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion and your hero.
flavorText: Might take a few episodes to power up.

name: Spirit Claws
text: Has +2 Attack while you have Spell Damage.
flavorText: They'll be MUCH easier to use once they add the spiritthumb.

name: Spirit of the Badlands
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, get a permanent Mirage.
flavorText: That's the spirit! Of the Badlands.

name: Spirit of the Team
text: Stealth for 1 turn. Your hero has +2 Attack on your turn.
flavorText: Horrible call! BOOOOoo00oO0o0OO0oo0oO!

name: Splendiferous Whizbang
text: You start the game with one of Whizbang's Experimental Decks!
flavorText: After his work at Boomsday Labs, he's taken what Dr. Boom taught him and applied it to the most important inventions of all - TOYS!!!

name: Splish-Splash Whelp
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, gain an empty Mana Crystal.
flavorText: Little Whelpy, you're the one You make Mana lots of fun

name: Spot the Difference
text: Discover a 3-Cost minion to summon. If your deck has no minions, repeat this.
flavorText: Ah, I see now! One of them is a picture of a Chillwind Yeti, and the other is a Blood Elf.

name: Spotlight
text: Tradeable Convert a friendly Divine Shield into a 5/5 Elemental.
flavorText: Everyone's eyes are on you! Well, they're also looking at the giant Elemental that we're using as a spotlight, but mainly at you!

name: Spread the Word
text: Draw 2 cards. Costs (1) less for each Attack your hero has.
flavorText: W O R D

name: Spurfang
text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Summon a random Beast with Cost equal to this minion's Attack.
flavorText: He's always smiling… Not by choice, but because it hurts to close his mouth.

name: Staff of the Primus
text: After your hero attacks, shuffle a random Plague into your opponent's deck.
flavorText: THE PRIMUS, RULER OF MALDRAXXUS, MASTER STRATEGIST, AND wielder of toothpicks!

name: Stand Against Darkness
text: Summon five 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits.
flavorText: Or if you're too tired, you can just kind of lean against the darkness.

name: Star Power
text: Deal 5 damage to a random enemy minion. Repeat this with 1 less damage.
flavorText: Five of the spectators were star-struck.

name: Stargazer Luna
text: After you play the right-most card in your hand, draw a card.
flavorText: She's Dr. Boom's right-hand mage.

name: Stargazing
text: Draw a different Arcane spell. If you play it this turn, it casts twice.
flavorText: See those dots up there? Those are called "stars." Except for that one. That's called an "airplane."

name: Starlight Groove
text: Give your hero Divine Shield. For the rest of the game, playing a Holy spell refreshes it.
flavorText: In space, no one can hear you groove.

name: Starlight Whelp
text: Battlecry: Get a random card from your starting hand.
flavorText: Starlight, star bright, first whelp I see tonight.

name: Starshooter
text: After your hero attacks, get an Arcane Shot.
flavorText: Shoot for the stars! And if you miss, just don't hit me.

name: Starstrung Bow
text: Costs (1) less for each friendly Secret that has triggered this game.
flavorText: Shoot for the stars, but if you miss, aim for the enemy hero.

name: Static Waveform
text: At the start of EACH turn, lose 1 Attack or Health (chosen randomly).
flavorText: LET ME SEE YOU MAKE SOME NOISE!!!

name: Steam Guardian
text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. Reduce the Cost of a Fire spell in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Its boiling steam and erupting magma serve as a pretty good form of 2-Factor Authentication.

name: Stereo Totem
text: At the end of your turn, give a random minion in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: Pass the ox cord!

name: Stick Up
text: Discover a Quickdraw card from another class.
flavorText: Dude, Velarok, give me a minute to play my turn, the rope's burning!

name: Stitched Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each Corpse you've spent this game.
flavorText: Sew big or go home!

name: Stone Drake
text: Divine Shield, Taunt, Lifesteal, Elusive
flavorText: "I am the great Stone Drake - good morning!"

name: Stoneheart King
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 2/2 Earthen that gains +2/+2 for each other Earthen you've summoned this game.
flavorText: I, too, am a king at playing Heart Stone.

name: Stonehill Defender
text: Taunt Battlecry: Discover a Taunt minion.
flavorText: Briefly tried stand-up comedy under the name "Stonehill Offender", but turtles are just too thin-skinned.

name: Stoneskin Armorer
text: Battlecry: If your Armor changed this turn, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: Pretty sensitive for someone made of thick skin.

name: Storm Giant
text: Taunt Forge: Costs (2) less. Can be Forged endlessly.
flavorText: Storm Giant, Frost Giant, Molten Giant... I want Fair-weather and Sunshine Giant!

name: Stormwind Champion
text: Your other minions have +1/+1.
flavorText: When Deathwing assaulted the capital, this soldier was the only member of his squad to survive. Now he's all bitter and stuff.

name: Stranglethorn Heart
text: Tradeable Resurrect all friendly Beasts that cost (5) or more.
flavorText: The Stranglethorn mentality is to be happy with the bare necessities.

name: Stranglethorn Tiger
text: Stealth
flavorText: The wonderful thing about tigers is tigers are wonderful things!

name: Student of the Stars
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle a copy of this into your deck with permanent +3/+3.
flavorText: She is getting her major in Ursa.

name: Summer Flowerchild
text: Battlecry: Draw two cards that cost (6) or more. Finale: They cost (1) less.
flavorText: "Ugh, those Winter Floweradults just don't get our music."

name: Summoning Ward
text: Secret: When your turn starts, summon a copy of your highest Cost minion.
flavorText: You couldn't handle one Snowflipper Penguin. So what hope do you have… against two?!

name: Sunset Volley
text: Deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies. Summon a random 10-Cost minion.
flavorText: When the light is just right during Golden Hour, that is when you take out the selfie stick and start casting.

name: Sunspot Dragon
text: Tradeable, Lifesteal Quickdraw: Deal 6 damage.
flavorText: THIS is why you shouldn't look directly at the sun.

name: Swarm of Lightbugs
text: Summon 10 1/1 Lightbugs with Lifesteal. Save any excess in a 1-Cost Bottle.
flavorText: No, I asked for 'lightNING in a bottle'!

name: Swashburglar
text: Battlecry: Add a random card from another class to your hand.
flavorText: Was almost named "Swashb-AAAARRHHH-gler"

name: Sweetened Snowflurry
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Get 2 random temporary Frost spells.
flavorText: "You want a piece of me!? Will that be one scoop or two?"

name: Swipe
text: Deal 4 damage to an enemy and 1 damage to all other enemies.
flavorText: When a bear rears back and extends his arms, he's about to Swipe! ... or hug.

name: Sylvanas Windrunner
text: Deathrattle: Take control of a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Sylvanas was turned into the Banshee Queen by Arthas, but he probably should have just killed her because it just pissed her off.

name: Symphony of Sins
text: Discover and play a Movement. Shuffle the other 6 into your deck.
flavorText: Makes for some killer final boss music.

name: Synthesize
text: Add a random 1, 2, and 3-Cost Elemental to your hand.
flavorText: After the invention of elemental audio processing, Azeroth went through a major synth phase.

name: Table Flip
text: Deal 3 damage to all enemy minions. Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
flavorText: "Judge!"

name: Tabletop Roleplayer
text: Miniaturize Battlecry: Give a friendly Demon +2 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: "And then I uh... I curse them with... uh... OH! I got it! They have to speak in rhymes or they turn into a crab!"

name: Tae'thelan Bloodwatcher
text: Cards that didn't start in your deck cost (4) less (but not less than 1).
flavorText: He's a big fan of Control Death Knight live streams.

name: Taelan Fordring
text: Taunt, Divine Shield Deathrattle: Draw your highest Cost minion.
flavorText: After growing up with the Scarlet Crusade for most of his life, Taelan finally realized they were maybe not the nicest people.

name: Tainted Remnant
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, deal 7 damage randomly split between all enemies.
flavorText: A sore sight of eyesores for sore eyes.

name: Take to the Skies
text: Draw two Dragons. Give them +1/+1.
flavorText: This is one step above reaching for the skies.

name: Tar Creeper
text: Taunt Has +2 Attack during your opponent's turn.
flavorText: If you won't come to the tar pits, we'll bring them to you!

name: Tar Slick
text: Minions take double damage this turn. Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: Has +2 Attack on its opponent's turn.

name: Tar Slime
text: Taunt Has +2 Attack during your opponent's turn.
flavorText: Too cute to be contained!

name: Taste of Chaos
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Finale: Discover a Fel spell.
flavorText: It's spicy!

name: Tempest Hammer
text: After your hero attacks, deal 3 damage to the lowest Health enemy.
flavorText: LIKE SWATTING PESTS!

name: Ten Gallon Hat
text: Draw a minion. Give it +1/+1 and "Deathrattle: Get a Ten Gallon Hat."
flavorText: It actually only holds three quarters of a gallon, but that doesn't sound as good.

name: Tentacle Grip
text: Deal 3 damage. Combo: Get a 1/1 Chaotic Tendril.
flavorText: "WINTER VEIL WAS MONTHS AGO, WHY ARE YOUR LIGHTS STILL UP?"

name: Tentacle Tender
text: At the end of your turn, get a 1/1 Chaotic Tendril.
flavorText: It's a messy job but somebody's got to do it. Well, actually, nobody should do this.

name: Tess Greymane
text: Battlecry: Replay every card from another class you've played this game (targets chosen randomly).
flavorText: Those who cannot remember their card history are doomed to repeat it.

name: Testing Dummy
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Deal 8 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Don't worry, they're having a blast. MUAHAHAHAHAAAA!

name: Thassarian
text: Reborn Battlecry and Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: A natural born leader. And an unnatural reborn leader.

name: The Badlands Bandits
text: Get eight 3/2 Bandits with bonus effects. Any that can't fit in your hand are summoned instead.
flavorText: Bandits... ASSEMBLE!

name: The Crystal Cove
text: The next minion you summon this turn has its stats set to 5/5.
flavorText: For some strange reason, everyone that hangs out at the Crystal Cove has the same name...

name: The Galactic Projection Orb
text: Recast a random spell of each Cost you've cast this game (targets enemies if possible).
flavorText: Look closely in the ball and you'll see the expansion of space and time itself. Or their projections, anyway.

name: The Headless Horseman
text: Battlecry: Destroy the enemy minion with the most Attack! Shuffle my Head into your deck, you must get it back!
flavorText: This flavor text, you would expect to rhyme and reference, to great effect! It starts out strong, but as you can tell it doesn't end very good.

name: The One-Amalgam Band
text: Battlecry: Gain a random bonus effect for each minion of a different type you've played this game. ( )
flavorText: Why be good with ONE instrument when you can be terrible with ALL of them!!!

name: The Primus
text: Titan After this uses an ability, Discover a card with that Rune.
flavorText: As there is a Pantheon of titans, so is there also a Pantheon of Death, comprised of powerful rulers in the Shadowlands.

name: The Scourge
text: Fill your board with random Undead.
flavorText: “You speak of justice? Of cowardice? I will show you the justice of the grave and the true meaning of fear.”

name: The Stars Align
text: Transform minions in your hand into ones that cost (3) more. (They keep their original Cost.)
flavorText: Sweet, three Desert Obelisks!

name: Theldurin the Lost
text: Battlecry: If your deck started with no duplicates, gain Immune this turn and attack all enemies.
flavorText: He might be lost, but he knows where you can find these hands.

name: Therazane
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Double the stats of all Elementals in your hand and deck.
flavorText: You thought we forgot about her, didn't you? *nervous laughter*

name: Thickhide Kodo
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: The introduction of professions was devastating for kodo populations.

name: Thing from Below
text: Taunt Costs (1) less for each Totem you've summoned this game.
flavorText: Just can't resist the opportunity to hang around with a bunch of totems.

name: Thirsty Drifter
text: Taunt Costs (1) less for each 1-Cost card you've played this game.
flavorText: Quick! Someone bring her a Manathirst card!

name: Thistle Tea Set
text: Discover a spell from another class. Get a copy of it.
flavorText: Available with Swiftthistle or Decafthistle.

name: Thorignir Drake
text: Rush Whenever this attacks, summon two 3/1 Whelps to attack the target first.
flavorText: Throwing your children at enemies qualifies you for Worst Mother of the Year.

name: Thorim, Stormlord
text: Battlecry: Unlock your Overloaded Mana Crystals. Draw that many cards.
flavorText: In the mountains.

name: Thornmantle Musician
text: Finale: The next Beast you summon gets +1/+1.
flavorText: She calls the hyena her "little chef". Not sure what that's about.

name: Thornveil Tentacle
text: Lifesteal Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Jennifer dumped me.

name: Thrall's Gift
text: Discover a temporary Lightning Storm, Hex, or Bloodlust.
flavorText: "I wrapped it myself!" -Thrall

name: Threads of Despair
text: Give all minions "Deathrattle: Deal 1 damage to all minions."
flavorText: Mom, I frew up...

name: Thrive in the Shadows
text: Discover a spell from your deck.
flavorText: Why would your spells be afraid of the dark? It's easier to nap there.

name: Through Fel and Flames
text: Give a minion Rush. Finale: And +1/+1.
flavorText: It's a Fel spell, but also a FIRE spell.

name: Thunderbringer
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon an Elemental and Beast from your deck.
flavorText: You can lead a horse to water, but you can't stop it from electrocuting everything in the water.

name: Tigress Plushy
text: Miniaturize Rush, Lifesteal, Divine Shield
flavorText: The sheervalue of this card is undeniable.

name: Timber Tambourine
text: Deathrattle: Summon 5/5 (Ancient, Ancients). (Play cards that cost (5) or more while equipped to improve!)
flavorText: Timberine anyone? TIMBERINE!?

name: Time-Lost Protodrake
text: Taunt When you draw this, add a random Dragon to your hand.
flavorText: Weird way to say "late" but ok.

name: Timewinder Zarimi
text: Battlecry: Once per game, if you've summoned 8 other Dragons, take an extra turn. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: With how generous Whizbang's return policy is, Zarimi has never been busier.

name: Tiny Worldbreaker
text: Battlecry: If you control another Mech, deal 4 damage.
flavorText: "I'm doing my part!"

name: Tirion Fordring
text: Divine Shield, Taunt Deathrattle: Equip a 5/3 Ashbringer.
flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

name: Titanforged Traps
text: Discover and cast a Secret. Forge: Do it twice.
flavorText: Always place it underneath their health pack.

name: Tomb Traitor
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Plague in your opponent's deck to deal 3 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: You enjoy raiding, I enjoying traitoring. We are not the same.

name: Tony, King of Piracy
text: Battlecry: Replace your deck with a copy of your opponent's. Finale: Draw a card.
flavorText: Tony prefers sailing on torrents rather than streams.

name: Tough Crowd
text: Outcast: Return a minion to its owner's hand.
flavorText: "Your music's bad and you should feel bad."

name: Town Crier
text: Battlecry: Draw a Rush minion from your deck.
flavorText: When he was younger, he was the town crybaby.

name: Toy Boat
text: After you summon a Pirate, draw a card.
flavorText: Try playing seven of these in one turn fast.

name: Toy Captain Tarim
text: Miniaturize Taunt. Battlecry: Set a minion's Attack and Health to this minion's.
flavorText: Whizbang is now the sole proprietor of Un'Goro.

name: Toyrannosaurus
text: Rush Deathrattle: Deal 7 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: This toy WRECKS.

name: Toyrantus
text: Taunt, Elusive Battlecry: If you have 10 Mana Crystals, gain +7/+7.
flavorText: Dr. Boom was definitely a dinosaur kid.

name: Tracking
text: Discover a card from your deck.
flavorText: For the person who just cannot decide what card to put into a deck!

name: Tram Conductor Gerry
text: Battlecry: If you've Excavated twice, summon six 3/3 Tram Cars with Rush.
flavorText: His name is pronounced like 'gif'.

name: Tram Heist
text: Get a copy of each card your opponent played last turn.
flavorText: How are they gunna steal the whole tram!?

name: Tram Mechanic
text: Deathrattle: Get a Barrel of Sludge. TOXIC WASTE: Handle with care.
flavorText: He looks at life through sludge-tinted glasses.

name: Tram Operator
text: Battlecry: Draw a Mech. The next Mech you play costs (2) less.
flavorText: The guy in the back is screaming… because the train ride is so fun!

name: Trapdoor Spider
text: Stealth, Poisonous After your opponent plays a minion, attack it.
flavorText: I can respect that they're important for the ecosystem, as long as you keep them waaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaay over there.

name: Treasure Distributor
text: After you summon a Pirate, give it and this minion +1 Attack.
flavorText: As the illiterate pirates always say: There is no 'I' in 'piracy'.

name: Trial by Fire
text: Summon five 1/1 Val'kyr with Rush. When one dies, give the others +1/+1.
flavorText: Well, in ya go.

name: Trinket Artist
text: Battlecry: Draw a Divine Shield minion and an Aura.
flavorText: Many Draenei found new hobbies on the long journey from Argus.

name: Triple Sevens
text: Deal 7 damage to a minion. Draw 7 cards.
flavorText: If you count the 'seven' in the name, there's actually four total 7s, not three. Huge oversight from the designers.

name: Triplewick Trickster
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy, three times.
flavorText: You no take candle! Or second candle. You can take third candle though.

name: Trogg Exile
text: Rush Battlecry: Deal 4 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Trogg used to rule…

name: Trogg Gemtosser
text: Finale: Deal 1 damage to a random enemy for each of your Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Oh no! You're throwing valuable gems at me! Please stop!

name: Trolley Problem
text: Discard your lowest Cost spell. Summon two 3/3 Tram Cars with Rush. Quickdraw: Don't discard.
flavorText: If only there were thousands of hypotheticals to prepare me for this moment!

name: Trusty Companion
text: Give a minion +2/+3. If it has a minion type, draw one of that type.
flavorText: Textbook big-sibling and little-sibling relationship.

name: Turn the Tides
text: Give your hero +3 Attack this turn. Summon a 3/3 Elemental with Rush. Overload: (1)
flavorText: T I D E S

name: Twilight Drake
text: Battlecry: Gain +1 Health for each card in your hand.
flavorText: Twilight drakes feed on Mystical Energy. And Tacos.

name: Twilight Torrent
text: Choose a character. If it's friendly, restore 6 Health. If it's an enemy, deal 3 damage.
flavorText: I hope it’s the first one.

name: Twisted Frostwing
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon a Chimaera with stats equal to this minion's Attack.
flavorText: Not currently valid in the Twist format.

name: Twisting Nether
text: Destroy all minions and locations.
flavorText: The Twisting Nether is a formless place of magic and illusion and destroyed minions.

name: Tyr
text: Battlecry: Resurrect a 2, 3, and 4-Attack minion from your class.
flavorText: Brought me back to life, S Tyr card.

name: Tyr's Tears
text: Resurrect 3 different minions from your class. Set their stats to 2/2. Forge: Resurrect another.
flavorText: Liek this if u cri evertim

name: Umberwing
text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Felwings.
flavorText: Demon Hunters refer to these glaives as "the ol’ flappy-attackys."

name: Umpire's Grasp
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Demon and reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: PENALTY - FEL BALL!

name: Unchained Gladiator
text: Battlecry: Draw a card. Repeat for each Elemental you played last turn. ( )
flavorText: We can't possibly buff this card any more, just look at him!

name: Unlucky Powderman
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Give Taunt minions in your hand and deck +1/+1.
flavorText: Welp, guess I'll die... again.

name: Unpopular Has-Been
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random 5-Cost minion from the past.
flavorText: Oh man, she used to rock more than ANYONE back in the Year of the Kraken. I wish I could've seen her perform back then…

name: Uther's Gift
text: Discover a temporary Equality, Consecration, or Blessing of Kings.
flavorText: "I hope you enjoy light reading!" -Uther

name: V-07-TR-0N Prime
text: T1T4N This minion's abilities repeat on another random friendly minion.
flavorText: Long after the titans' departure, Mimiron dreamed of creating something with an approximation of their power. He may have actually succeeded!

name: Valeera's Gift
text: Discover a temporary Backstab, Deadly Poison, or Fan of Knives.
flavorText: "Here. You. Go." -Valeera

name: Vampiric Blood
text: Give your hero +5 Health. Spend 3 Corpses to gain 5 more and draw a card.
flavorText: BLEH, BLEH BLEH!

name: Velarok Windblade
text: While this is in your hand, play a card from another class to reveal Velarok's true form!
flavorText: His deceptive manipulations have dug the Bloodrock Company into a hole they can't get out of.

name: Verse Riff
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Gain 2 Armor. Finale: Play your last Riff.
flavorText: Well anyways, here's Worgen Wall.

name: Vicious Slitherspear
text: After you cast a spell, gain +1 Attack until your next turn.
flavorText: He goes by ‘Fun-Loving Slitherspear’ on his dating profile.

name: Victorious Vrykul
text: After this attacks, get a 2/3 Val'kyr that costs (1).
flavorText: Get three of these and you have a Trikul.

name: Void Scripture
text: Discover a spell. If you have enough Mana to play it, cast a copy of it at a random enemy.
flavorText: The Old Gods like to think of them as "Addendums."

name: Void Shard
text: Lifesteal Deal 4 damage.
flavorText: Light's easy. Void's hard.

name: Void Virtuoso
text: During your turn, your hero is Immune.
flavorText: That is one interesting dress code.

name: Voidwalker
text: Taunt
flavorText: No relation to "The Voidsteppers", the popular Void-based dance troupe.

name: Volume Up
text: Draw 3 spells. Finale: Discover a copy of one.
flavorText: You have to pay Mana to do that!? I thought it was just in the settings menu!

name: Voodoo Doctor
text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health.
flavorText: Voodoo is an oft-misunderstood art. But it is art.

name: Vulpera Scoundrel
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell or pick a mystery choice.
flavorText: A spell is a spell, but the mystery choice could be anything! (It's also a spell.)

name: Walking Mountain
text: Rush, Lifesteal, Mega-Windfury Overload: (2)
flavorText: The hills are alive with the sound of YEEEEHAAAWWWW!

name: Wandmaker
text: Battlecry: Add a 1-Cost spell from your class to your hand.
flavorText: She creates incredibly affordable wands of all shapes and sizes. But not owls. The owl is all-natural.

name: Wargear
text: Magnetic
flavorText: WAR! GEAR! What is it good for?

name: Warhorse Trainer
text: Your Silver Hand Recruits have +2 Attack and Taunt.
flavorText: He doesn't even get Sundays off. Every day he's hostling.

name: Warsong Grunt
text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, it may attack again.
flavorText: Where do you think the chickens learned to be angry?

name: Waste Remover
text: At the end of your turn, destroy the bottom 3 cards of your deck.
flavorText: Always follow the three Rs: REDUCE their world to ash, REUSE their bones as paperweights, and RECYCLE!

name: Watcher of the Sun
text: Battlecry: Get a random Holy spell. Forge: Also restore 6 Health to your hero.
flavorText: "I've got my eye on y-AAA I'M BLIND!"

name: Watercannon
text: After your hero attacks, summon a 1/1 Pirate that attacks a random enemy.
flavorText: There's a teeny tiny pirate trapped in each of the water balloons. Free them!

name: Watercolor Artist
text: Battlecry: Draw a Frost spell. At the start of your turns, reduce its Cost by (1).
flavorText: They've amassed a largely aquatic body of work, painting lakes, rivers and self portraits.

name: Wayward Sage
text: Outcast: Reduce the Cost of the left and right-most cards in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Carry on my wayward sage. There'll be peace and no more rage.

name: Weight of the World
text: Draw 2 cards. Forge: Draw cards until you have as many in hand as your opponent first.
flavorText: Unluckily for him, Azeroth has a tendency to get bigger every 2 years or so.

name: Wheel of DEATH!!!
text: Destroy your deck. In 5 turns, destroy the enemy hero.
flavorText: Why don't the good guys ever get a wheel?

name: Whelp Wrangler
text: At the end of your turn, get a 1/2 Whelp with Taunt.
flavorText: "Gosh darn it! How did these winged, airborne creatures manage to escape my knee-high, fenced enclosure AGAIN!?"

name: Whirlwind
